Dialogue: 10,0:00:29.81,0:00:34.01,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,April of 1957.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:34.01,0:00:37.98,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Once again, the city of Osaka \Nwas swept up in the national elections.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:39.29,0:00:41.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The by-election for the House of Councillors
Dialogue: 10,0:00:41.79,0:00:45.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in the Osaka constituency \Nwas announced on March 29th.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:45.98,0:00:50.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Though the race lacked excitement \Nwith eight candidates vying for a single seat,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:50.21,0:00:54.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Oyama Tatsuzo, endorsed by the Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:54.47,0:00:57.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,campaigned passionately throughout the prefecture,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:57.98,0:01:02.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,steadily winning over voters with his policies.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:05.84,0:01:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to talk about \Nthe fundamentals of our next battle.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:09.82,0:01:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,First and foremost: \Nelection fraud will not be tolerated.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:14.28,0:01:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Second: our religious guidance \Ncannot be shallow. {lit: we'll plan a thorough faith guidance}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:18.16,0:01:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Third: don't take the elections lightly. {lit: the thoroughness of the significance of holding elections}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:21.23,0:01:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As citizens of this nation, it's our duty to campaign with everything we've got—
Dialogue: 10,0:01:25.80,0:01:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,within the bounds of election law—and I'm certain that doing so will lead us to victory!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:31.82,0:01:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:33.24,0:01:36.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As the mid-April by-election entered its final stretch,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.68,0:01:40.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the race grew increasingly chaotic amid an unexpected surge
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.27,0:01:42.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in support for candidate Oyama.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.29,0:01:46.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Oyama's campaign promises \Nstruck a chord with voters,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.72,0:01:53.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the growing wave of popular support \Nfor him began to rattle his rivals.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.55,0:01:56.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Pitted against the two major parties—\Nthe Liberals and the Socialists—
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.88,0:02:00.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Oyama was initially dismissed \Nas a long-shot, desperation candidate.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.98,0:02:04.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, the race has turned into a fierce three-way battle,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.50,0:02:07.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with the outcome now anyone’s guess.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.58,0:02:13.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was then, on April 22nd, \Nthe day before the election,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.02,0:02:18.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,during the final stretch of the campaigning efforts, when a sudden incident occurred.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.45,0:02:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:19.62,0:02:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone was handing out cigarettes
Dialogue: 10,0:02:22.19,0:02:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with Oyama's name on them in front \Nof the employment office in Taisho Ward?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:25.70,0:02:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it's important! \NGet in touch with Chief Yamamoto at once!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.54,0:02:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Also bring those cigarettes \Nto the Kansai Headquarters!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.78,0:02:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Combining on-site reports and the evening news, this is what we know to date.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.01,0:02:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Early this morning, a man arrived by taxi at four employment offices
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.98,0:02:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in Taisho, Nishi, Minato, and Fukushima wards, handing out to the day laborers gathered there {daily employment; hiring by the day; day laborer; day labourer}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.60,0:02:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds of packs of {\i1}Pearl Light{\i0} cigarettes.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.03,0:02:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he disappeared on the streets.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.78,0:03:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oyama’s name, written in katakana, \Nwas printed on the flaps of those cigarette packs.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.05,0:03:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's one pack as a proof.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.04,0:03:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.88,0:03:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{Huh?}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.61,0:03:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.01,0:03:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Reportedly, around 8 p.m. tonight, \Nsomeone was seen distributing 100-yen bills
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.72,0:03:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,attached to Oyama’s business cards \Nin the Ajiro area of Fuse City
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.83,0:03:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and along Katsuyama Street in Ikuno Ward.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.02,0:03:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems they were also distributing them \Nto passersby while riding bicycles
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.89,0:03:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,around Shigino in Joto Ward \Nand Nagare in Oyodo Ward.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.09,0:03:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They even went that far?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.49,0:03:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief! It’s got to be another party trying to discredit Oyama-san in the eyes of the voters.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.96,0:03:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's gotta be it!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.39,0:03:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, immediately contact the Election Security Office {of the Osaka Prefectural Police }
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.73,0:03:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and file a protest in the name \Nof Oyama’s Election Office.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.29,0:03:54.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On election day, the 23rd,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.21,0:03:59.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,all the morning newspapers ran headline stories \Nabout this major bribery scandal.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.51,0:04:03.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With Oyama’s reputation in shambles \Nand now at a huge disadvantage,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.57,0:04:06.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,they could only watch \Nas the polls closed as usual.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.44,0:04:14.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That day, on his way back from a lecture in Kyushu, Toda stopped by the Kansai HQ
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.09,0:04:17.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and waited in the president’s office \Nfor the election results.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.87,0:04:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okawa Mitsuzo, LDP. \N239,409 votes. {not sure what to make of 自民新}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.26,0:04:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Murao Shigeo, SDP. \N236,880 votes.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.79,0:04:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oyama Tatsuzo, non-partisan. \N151,823 votes.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.44,0:04:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The gap is a lot more than before!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.26,0:04:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.07,0:04:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.77,0:04:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.83,0:04:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How was it?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.69,0:04:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.95,0:04:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We lost. {not selected}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.05,0:05:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, please forgive us.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.19,0:05:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I have disgraced you. {/lost face}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.50,0:05:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to request dismissal from all of my current positions.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.73,0:05:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.83,0:05:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, in a battle you always win or lose. \NThat’s the nature of battle.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.11,0:05:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But you live to fight another day. \NFight to the bitter end!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.65,0:05:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.18,0:05:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, forgive me!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.33,0:05:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Someday, I'll definitely put up a fight \Nthat'll take the world by storm! {lit: astound the world without losing anywhere}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.74,0:05:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.36,0:05:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I wanted to hear.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.66,0:05:47.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so, within less than a year of his assignment to Osaka,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.17,0:05:54.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi tasted both the thrill of a triumphant election win and the sting of a heartbreaking loss.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.63,0:05:59.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.59,0:06:03.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,"The Coal Miners' Union has resolved \Nto take measures against new religious groups?"
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.55,0:06:12.51,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Among the many labor organizations, one stood out for its formidable sway across Japan—
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.51,0:06:15.56,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,especially in the coal mining regions \Nof Kyushu and Hokkaido:
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.56,0:06:21.78,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the Japan Coal Miners' Union, said to be so fearsome it could silence even a crying child.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.33,0:06:25.80,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,At the 17th regular meeting of the Coal Miners' Union,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.80,0:06:29.12,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,held at the Central Labor Relations Committee Hall in Shiba, Tokyo,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.12,0:06:34.16,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,a new policy of countermeasures against emerging religious groups was adopted—
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.16,0:06:37.27,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,chiefly aimed at Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.27,0:06:39.44,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,This is outrageous.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.44,0:06:41.44,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,When I went to Yubari in January,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.44,0:06:45.24,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,I heard about bullying and mistreatment of the members among miners.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.24,0:06:50.04,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,And now that institutionalized injustice \Nis bound to become even more prevalent.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.96,0:06:53.06,Top,,0,0,0,,Mitsubayashi-san, Arakawa-san,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.06,0:06:57.73,Top,,0,0,0,,what exactly entails this "unjustified oppression \Nand harassment" by the miners' union?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.73,0:07:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for example, small loans from labor banks require approval from the welfare commission.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.01,0:07:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But the union leaders never allow that.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.41,0:07:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Some even openly say, "We'll only lend to you if you renounce Soka Gakkai."
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.53,0:07:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.54,0:07:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that, but when we apply \Nfor roof repairs to the miner barracks we live in
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.25,0:07:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or ask for new mats, our comrades are always sidelined or even told they don't care.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.13,0:07:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's terrible.\NWhy would they do that?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.09,0:07:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's because we didn't support the candidate that the union endorsed
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.45,0:07:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the last House of Councillors election.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.06,0:07:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But even the Coal Miners' Union has no right \Nto interfere with one's right to vote.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.50,0:07:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also a violation of our constitutionally protected freedom of religion.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.40,0:07:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.34,0:07:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't directly say \Nit was because of the election,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.41,0:07:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but they resented the significant drop \Nin the union's votes
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.57,0:07:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and blamed the Soka Gakkai members
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.87,0:07:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,for weakening the union's power and disrupting worker unity.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.10,0:08:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, we've been subjected \Nto constant harassment and oppression.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.98,0:08:09.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,Either way, Soka Gakkai will have \Nto step in and resolve that issue for good.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.75,0:08:42.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, let's face them! \NWe've not done anything wrong!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.61,0:08:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We've seen your invitation. \NNow what?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.98,0:09:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We want anyone who disrupts the union's authority to leave the union immediately.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.00,0:09:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.90,0:09:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! When and where did anyone ever disrupt their control?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.52,0:09:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't play dumb! Try to think about it, \Nwith your hand on your heart!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.61,0:09:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, let's not get emotional, \Nor this conversation won't go anywhere.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.62,0:09:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try to talk things over calmly. \NSit down, please.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.25,0:09:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.02,0:09:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just full of hot air! {lit: What you're saying is bullshit}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.86,0:09:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can substantiate that! {literal, but sounds too cumbersome to me; dunno what to do about it either tho, so your chance to shine, paul}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.01,0:09:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding me? Soka Gakkai always opposes the union's policies!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.47,0:09:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's new. {lit: that is a strange story}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.87,0:09:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, during labor{-management} disputes,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.75,0:09:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't Soka Gakkai members \Nalways stood with the other union members?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.87,0:09:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Your argument is incredulous!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.28,0:09:50.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The talks went nowhere \Nand ended without any resolution.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.06,0:10:00.08,Top,,0,0,0,,That's the situation in Yubari, according to both branch heads—Mitsubayashi and Arakawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.08,0:10:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to move quickly to guarantee
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.51,0:10:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that Soka Gakkai members on-site \Ncan practice their faith safely. {not on work site but as in "in the area"}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.71,0:10:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, very well. \NSend the youth division leaders.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.28,0:10:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be ready to fly at any time too.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.39,0:10:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that was my plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.60,0:10:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it's incredible how wrong \Nthe Miners' Union is. {wrong (guess or estimate); misdirected; irrelevant; off the point}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.72,0:10:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Labor and religious organizations \Nhave completely different goals and duties.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.21,0:10:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And since our spheres of interest \Nare so different, {/standings}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.04,0:10:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no reason for us \Nto interfere with each other.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.42,0:10:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What a weird happening indeed...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.16,0:10:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{Phew...}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.04,0:10:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The work is finally done and dusted with.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.67,0:10:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if there's been any interesting news...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.54,0:10:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh? What the hell!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.65,0:10:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"The cigarette handout incident and the 100 yen \Nnote incident were Soka Gakkai's doing?!"
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.97,0:10:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Damned if we let them \Nget away with this bollocks!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.72,0:11:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta let Branch Chief Haruki know at once!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.83,0:11:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday evening's paper reported that Omura Masato, a Soka Gakkai district chief,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.05,0:11:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,was the mastermind behind the pre-election cigarette and 100-yen bill handout incidents.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.51,0:11:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.45,0:11:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Four have been arrested already.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:23.89,0:11:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The investigation revealed that Omura and 30 others handed out cigarettes {not sure if "paper's investigation" or police's}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.56,0:11:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of 10 prefectural employment offices \Non the morning before the election,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.07,0:11:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and that same evening, \Ndistributed 100-yen bills
Dialogue: 10,0:11:36.86,0:11:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,across Osaka and other areas \Nbefore retreating to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.10,0:11:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That Omura Masato... \NIf I remember correctly...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.91,0:11:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be the district head Omura \Nof the Kamata branch.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.90,0:11:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.26,0:11:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure he wasn't part \Nof the campaign team for this election.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.05,0:11:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.05,0:11:59.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.55,0:12:04.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,He was probably raring for recognition \Nand wanted to distinguish himself somehow... {lit: driven by ambition}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.88,0:12:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiyohara-san, I believe the leadership needs \Nto determine whether this was simply a reckless,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.44,0:12:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,unilateral act by a few overzealous members,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.89,0:12:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or part of a larger plot aimed at discrediting Soka Gakkai. Will you see to it?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.33,0:12:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly. Soka Gakkai needs to shed light \Non this and take immediate and firm action.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:29.48,0:12:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, start an investigation as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.96,0:12:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.82,0:12:36.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Hokkaido Coal Miners' Union adopted
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.38,0:12:39.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,a more aggressive stance toward Soka Gakkai, \Nescalating the hostility;
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.78,0:12:44.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,on June 27, it formed a special committee \Nto deal with dissidents for good
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.60,0:12:48.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and issued a directive to all branches \Nand coal mines across the prefecture,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.71,0:12:51.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,setting a firm deadline for the expulsion \Nof Soka Gakkai members.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.79,0:12:55.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Unaware of this, branch chief Mitsubayashi was on his way
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.67,0:12:58.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to the Yubari Miners' Union office that day.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.09,0:12:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.61,0:13:03.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With the persecution of Soka Gakkai members worsening by the day,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.88,0:13:07.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he resolved to meet the union president face-to-face to lodge a formal protest.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.57,0:13:10.27,Top,,0,0,0,,If it isn't Mitsubayashi-san!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.15,0:13:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, editor-in-chief! \NGood timing. {actually "[newspaper] branch chief"}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.96,0:13:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on my way to the miners' union office to issue a protest.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.42,0:13:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to come along?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.05,0:13:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good. Let's go.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.62,0:13:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you already! Get me the union executive—\NI need to talk to him personally!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.00,0:13:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what you believe in,\Nbut you'll need to stop proselytizing around here.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.77,0:13:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Your members are a thorn in our side!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.90,0:13:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? \NPropagation is the lifeblood of faith!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.45,0:13:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Our constitution also guarantees \Nthe freedom of proselytizing!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.30,0:13:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your union trying to obstruct it? \NIt's a violation of the constitution!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.72,0:13:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.81,0:13:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Our missionary work is aimed at saving as many people as we can from misery!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.17,0:13:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would we ever stop?!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.90,0:13:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for a moment...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.67,0:14:03.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,How cowardly can they be?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.78,0:14:08.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,The union executive is right there in that room, \Nbut he wouldn't even show himself!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.37,0:14:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mitsubayashi-san, this isn't going anywhere.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.06,0:14:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So what are we going to do?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.84,0:14:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We could arrange a formal meeting \Nto hold a discussion on this matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.51,0:14:24.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,A public debate, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.34,0:14:27.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, at this stage, \Nwe can't take a step back!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.62,0:14:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.87,0:14:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Just so we're clear—are you proposing a public debate between Soka Gakkai and your union?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.87,0:14:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That option is also among the possibilities.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.52,0:14:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine by me! A debate is fine. \NVery well, we accept it!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:40.47,0:14:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when and where \Nare we going to have it?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.01,0:14:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We will contact you again \Nfor details such as a date and the venue.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.04,0:14:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.94,0:14:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-chief, won't you be our witness? {to the arrangement/to the fact that they settled for a debate}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.54,0:14:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, happily.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.58,0:14:58.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Following that, the secretary-general \Nof the Yubari Miners' Union reached out to him
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.88,0:15:03.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and said, "We’d like to hold a debate on July 4th at the Yubari Labor Hall,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.50,0:15:07.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with ten representatives from each side."
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.79,0:15:10.06,Top,,0,0,0,,...That's what they said.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:10.06,0:15:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll tell everyone in Yubari.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.79,0:15:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about the Chief?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.00,0:15:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. We'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.53,0:15:23.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.07,0:15:29.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,I see... It all piled up on us at the same time?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.74,0:15:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears that the Osaka Prefectural Police are preparing
Dialogue: 10,0:15:33.67,0:15:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to charge Chairman Konishi and \NPR Department Chief Yamamoto with bribery
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.40,0:15:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and door-to-door canvassing.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.31,0:15:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.83,0:15:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on? Are they trying to frame these two for a crime they didn't commit?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.43,0:15:48.85,Top,,0,0,0,,The prosecutor is relentless. {lit: criminal investigation; prosecution is driven to the edge/desperate - think he means "they'll be persecuting them to the end of the world"}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.85,0:15:52.30,Top,,0,0,0,,I think it's safe to assume \Nthat they'll stop at nothing. {lit: it's better to think that they'll even go as far as stubbornness; obstinacy; willpower; pride}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.30,0:15:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, are they about to move in to arrest them? {/is our time near}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.95,0:15:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's what it looks like. {/according to the information}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.61,0:16:04.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,Let them come! \NI'll accept everything with a smile on my face.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.44,0:16:10.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Not only in Yubari, Hokkaido, but also in Osaka, the darkest cloud in Soka Gakkai’s history
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.54,0:16:17.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was gathering above it, with a storm brewing, ready to come crashing down all at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.29,0:16:23.50,Top,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be leaving for Sapporo now \Nto meet Chief Yamamoto.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.50,0:16:26.76,Top,,0,0,0,,Got it. I'll get everything prepared here.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.76,0:16:30.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, on the following day, the 29th,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.16,0:16:34.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,an unexpected development \Nhad turned the situation upside-down.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.72,0:16:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.66,0:16:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:36.48,0:16:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A man at the door says he’s the head of public relations for the Yubari Miners’ Union... {propaganda; publicity; public relations}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.63,0:16:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The Union's PR head? \NBut why so suddenly?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.09,0:16:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's meet him.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.30,0:16:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Sawada, I came here from Tokyo to help \Nwith the preparations for the upcoming debate.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.31,0:16:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,PR head, what was it \Nyou wanted to discuss?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.62,0:17:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... I'm not really sure how to put it...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.23,0:17:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,About the debate we scheduled yesterday—\Nwe'd like it postponed... indefinitely.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.56,0:17:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:09.40,0:17:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.20,0:17:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we were already planning \Nto launch a strike in July,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.93,0:17:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so we don't happen to have any time or resources \Nto prepare for debates and such.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:21.73,0:17:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.44,0:17:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Your side’s the one that proposed the debate. \NHell, you’re the one who started all this! {lit: you're the ones who picked a fight}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.71,0:17:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think {\i1}we{\i0}'ve got \Nno other business to tend to?! {/we're busy just the same}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.45,0:17:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I came all the way from Tokyo to do this, \Nand I can't return empty-handed! {/without a debate}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.82,0:17:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll hold it as planned!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.56,0:17:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, you have to understand. \NWe're really busy, you see. I said sorry, didn't I?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.77,0:17:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Arakawa-san, at least say something!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.71,0:17:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that ain't gonna do.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.48,0:17:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you thinking, harassing Soka Gakkai members all this time?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.86,0:17:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No backing out now!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.85,0:17:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way we can attend those debates! {あっ･･･対決だけは何としてもできませんから･･･}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.77,0:18:04.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,What’s with this sudden change of mind? \NWe need to inform Chief Yamamoto right away!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:06.13,0:18:08.48,Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone! How are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.48,0:18:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up and keep it that way. Now that I'm here, there's nothing to worry about. {lit: [keep] only bright/cheerful faces}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.01,0:18:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Have no worries, everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.79,0:18:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.28,0:18:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we lose in a fight for religious freedom and the happiness of the people?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.35,0:18:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We are sure to win!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.96,0:18:26.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The next day{, on the 30th}, Shinichi
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.98,0:18:32.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,requested a meeting with the Miners' Union’s PR head twice—in the morning and in the afternoon—
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.99,0:18:38.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but was {adamantly }turned down, first with the excuse \Nof a meeting, and later due to a reported fever.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.66,0:18:42.81,Top,,0,0,0,,I can relate to everyone's frustration \Nand anger all too keenly.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.81,0:18:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This abrupt shift in the Yubari Miners' Union’s stance
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.85,0:18:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,may have been directed by the Coal Miners' Union headquarters in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.71,0:18:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it dawned on them that the Union’s policy
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.15,0:18:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,infringes on the workers’ religious freedoms—\Nand might be deemed unconstitutional.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.01,0:19:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So they called off the debate at the last minute \Nas a form of damage control.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.70,0:19:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that they turned me down twice
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.68,0:19:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,makes it clear the union \Nhas lost all will to engage in a debate.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.40,0:19:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not the end of our troubles, \Nnot by a long shot.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.26,0:19:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The union will likely keep coming up with new methods to harass Soka Gakkai members.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.30,0:19:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why, this time, I’m determined to settle this once and for all—
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.45,0:19:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,so our comrades in Yubari are never subjected to mistreatment again.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.79,0:19:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll do it in the form of protest rallies \Nagainst the Miners’ Union—
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.17,0:19:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,one in Sapporo on July 1st, \Nand another in Yubari on July 2nd.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.99,0:19:41.29,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On June 30th, amidst the raging storm \Nof the Miners’ Union issue, {lit: evil storm of power}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.29,0:19:46.02,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the formation meeting \Nof the Soka Gakkai Student Division took place
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.02,0:19:48.46,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,at the Azabu Public Hall in Minato Ward, Tokyo,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.46,0:19:52.38,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,marking a new chapter\N in the history of the Common Path. {/page}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.88,0:19:56.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,The student division formation ceremony is to be held today.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.10,0:20:01.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,I should {at least }send the students a congratulatory telegram, wishing them a bright future.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.35,0:20:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We have received a congratulatory telegram from Chief Yamamoto in Yubari, Hokkaido.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.25,0:20:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Congratulations on the formation \Nof the Student Division,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.81,0:20:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where brilliant minds of the new century \Nhave come together. {/who are destined to lead soka gakkai into the new age}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.86,0:20:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Soar boldly into the world under President Toda’s leadership. —Yamamoto Shinichi”
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.01,0:20:22.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,So this is what the former nitpickers
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.20,0:20:26.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,from the Tokyo University \NLotus Sutra Study Group have grown into? {/quibblers/someone who raises a lot of questions}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.20,0:20:29.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,There's quite a lot of female students too...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.62,0:20:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Greetings from the Director of Student Affairs Shiroya!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.92,0:20:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope today marks a turning point for you—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.07,0:20:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,where you not only \Ndedicate yourselves to your studies,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:38.55,0:20:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but also bloom into true talents who distinguish themselves in Soka Gakkai activities.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.60,0:20:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone keeps saying \Nour student division is dwindling—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.48,0:20:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,yet here you are, \N500 bright minds strong. {meaning "there are 500 of you"}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.72,0:20:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can by no means call it a small number.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.92,0:20:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If only half of you become executives
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.88,0:21:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other half become professors, wouldn't that be more than enough? {think he means executives in general sense, as in "someone in power"}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.69,0:21:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can succeed in raising even that number of leaders,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.92,0:21:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that alone would surely throw into a tizzy \Nthose the world currently holds up as its leaders. {/... would lose their complexion/face color/expression}{unsure what he means: これだけの指導者ができたら それこそ今世間でリーダーと 仰がれている人たちは 全く顔色がなくなってしまうに 違いない}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.67,0:21:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I'm more than happy \Nwith this number.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.88,0:21:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You have my undivided support!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.86,0:21:21.91,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Moreover, on the 30th,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:21.91,0:21:28.31,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the authorities finally closed in on Shinichi’s inner circle with the intent to arrest him. {lit: to approach/press one's neighborhood/vicinity - not sure what's this about}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.31,0:21:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto needs to report himself to the Osaka Prefectural Police?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.67,0:21:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.25,0:21:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But right now it's impossible. \NPlease wait a day or two.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.84,0:21:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do this the hard way—\Nan arrest warrant won’t take long.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.28,0:21:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?! Yamamoto Shinichi \Nisn't trying to run away or hide!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.83,0:21:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What difference would a day or two \Nof delay make for you?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:49.06,0:21:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're saying we can come for him on July 3rd?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.39,0:21:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:53.38,0:21:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.26,0:21:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}am{\i0} sure!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.24,0:22:10.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,So the Osaka Police finally summoned me?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.82,0:22:14.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,Three days... All right, we can't lose this!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.81,0:22:17.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll fight them head on!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:18.61,0:22:22.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Sapporo rally opened at 6 p.m.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:22.99,0:22:27.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The 13,000 attendees who packed the hall \Nwere outraged by the revelations
Dialogue: 10,0:22:27.87,0:22:32.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of the Coal Miners’ persecution of Soka Gakkai members,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:32.26,0:22:35.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,making the convention a rousing success. {lit: the anger of members exploded and the rally was in high spirits}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:35.63,0:22:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Pointing to the drop in votes during the election,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:38.23,0:22:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,they’ve blamed Soka Gakkai members for the alleged anti-union behavior— {lit: disrupting the union’s organizational structure}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:41.73,0:22:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,even going so far as to unconstitutionally interfere with their religious activities!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:46.14,0:22:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As a society, we can by no means overlook it!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:49.93,0:22:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! That's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:50.55,0:22:51.45,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:54.71,0:22:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nichiren Daishonin said...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:03.78,0:23:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, by continually meditating and improving on the basics of your faith,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:09.28,0:23:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you can pave the way to success in your work or business and by extension—your personal growth.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:15.58,0:23:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why we strive to integrate our faith \Ninto every aspect of daily life—
Dialogue: 10,0:23:21.61,0:23:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,our work, our routines, \Nand our union activities. {probably means miners' union here even though he's not part of it himself}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:27.46,0:23:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the correct way forward \Nand the guiding principle of Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:32.27,0:23:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, the Miners’ Union \Nnot only refuses to understand this,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.47,0:23:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but has also aligned itself \Nwith destructive forces, {/demons}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.49,0:23:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,actively obstructing Soka Gakkai's efforts \Nto save the people and build a peaceful world.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.41,0:23:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This appearance of the three formidable enemies is proof that the fulfillment
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.82,0:23:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Common Path is near at hand!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:51.08,0:23:58.16,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On July 2nd, a demonstration march by the Soka Gakkai Youth Division began in Yubari City.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.16,0:24:00.97,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Young men from Tokyo and Sapporo
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.97,0:24:06.60,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,marched with pride and dignity through the city \Nalongside the Yubari Men’s Youth Division.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:07.22,0:24:09.70,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,We won't tolerate the union’s tyranny!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:09.70,0:24:15.31,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,We'll correct their wrongs and elevate \NSoka Gakkai's righteousness without flinching! {/promote soka gakkai's justice without taking a step back}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:15.93,0:24:19.94,Top,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai launched a protest against the union \Nwho can even silence a crying child!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:19.94,0:24:21.90,Top,,0,0,0,,Quite the nerve they've got...
Dialogue: 10,0:24:21.90,0:24:24.25,Top,,0,0,0,,Good luck, youth division boys!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:24.25,0:24:25.98,Top,,0,0,0,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:35.02,0:24:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Which branch are you from?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:36.38,0:24:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should we be from any branch? {/Which branch are we from?}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:37.75,0:24:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't outsiders join your little party?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:40.63,0:24:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There are separate seats prepared \Nfor non-Soka Gakkai members.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:44.98,0:24:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m a Yubari Miners’ Union executive—\NI came to hear your convention.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:49.11,0:24:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll let us in, won't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:50.82,0:24:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll arrange it now, please wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:54.31,0:24:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:56.19,0:24:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:59.15,0:25:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Yamamoto, in charge here. \NYou're welcome to attend.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:03.17,0:25:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I would ask you to listen patiently until we fully explain Soka Gakkai's position.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.92,0:25:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We can have a discussion afterwards.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:10.15,0:25:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:14.70,0:25:18.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then at 6 p.m., the Soka Gakkai Yubari Rally
Dialogue: 10,0:25:18.73,0:25:25.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,finally began at the Wakana Theater in Yubari, where the clash with the Miners' Union started. {/the birthplace of the Miner's Union issue}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:25.38,0:25:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The leaders of the Miners’ Union keep claiming they care about their members’ welfare,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:31.67,0:25:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but their actions show they’re only ever thinking about their own self-interest! {lit: just think about making themselves a little more important/greater - think maybe "only self-gratification"}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:37.06,0:25:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! Exactly!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:40.66,0:25:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:41.56,0:25:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you promise the Chief \Nto have a discussion afterwards? {/when it's over}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:45.17,0:25:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Something urgent just came to mind…
Dialogue: 10,0:25:47.74,0:25:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,P-Please wait a moment!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:49.97,0:25:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the Secretary General \Nof the Yubari Miners' Union, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:53.29,0:25:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you've come all the way here, \Nwhy don't we have a discussion?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:56.97,0:26:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually, there's an urgent matter waiting for me at home right now...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:01.25,0:26:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even for a short while?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:03.06,0:26:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm afraid not.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:04.98,0:26:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a shame. \NI hope I'll see you again.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:16.39,0:26:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With that said, \Nthe Yubari convention is concluded!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:20.94,0:26:25.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,This should see the Union issue \Nfinally settled for now. {think he means "this convinced the execs so they'll piss off even without debates"}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:27.61,0:26:30.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's July 3rd today...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:30.31,0:26:35.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right! July 3rd is the day \NToda-sensei was released from prison.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:36.14,0:26:42.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,And I'll be imprisoned on that same day... \NWhat an eerie coincidence.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:49.11,0:26:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin is not here yet?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:50.86,0:26:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be here soon enough. \NI hear the plane has just landed.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.07,0:27:02.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,When Konishi turned himself in to the Osaka {Prefectural }Police earlier, he was arrested immediately.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:03.04,0:27:07.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,If they're going to do the same to Shinichi next...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:07.19,0:27:11.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, who has to report to the Osaka Prefectural Police today,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:11.88,0:27:16.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,landed at Haneda Airport \Nto transfer to a flight to Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:16.89,0:27:19.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He had only a little time to transfer.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:20.09,0:27:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei is waiting for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:22.18,0:27:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? He's here?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:24.12,0:27:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:26.13,0:27:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just landed.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:27.58,0:27:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Shinichi...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:30.75,0:27:35.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,I ended up worrying Sensei so much...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:42.08,0:27:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A senior union official \Ncame to yesterday's rally in Yubari...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:45.94,0:27:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, they called me last night.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:49.21,0:27:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, you've done well. I mean it. {/good job/you've worked hard}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:56.16,0:27:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:59.43,0:28:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, keep going.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:02.83,0:28:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:04.16,0:28:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:06.38,0:28:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Our spiritual battle for the spread of Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism and the Common Path
Dialogue: 10,0:28:11.79,0:28:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,still needs to be fought in the real world. {unsure what he means: 日蓮大聖人の仏法を 広宣流布しようとする我々の戦いというのは 現実社会での格闘なのだ}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:14.91,0:28:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The deeper we plant our roots in the real world, \Nthe more resistance we’re bound to face.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:19.97,0:28:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That is something entirely unavoidable!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:22.93,0:28:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:24.56,0:28:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what difficulties arise, \Nwe have no choice but to fight back!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:29.42,0:28:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what great hardships lie ahead,\N Shinichi, keep going!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:36.03,0:28:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I will.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:38.47,0:28:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:39.86,0:28:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, how is your health?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:43.11,0:28:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:46.98,0:28:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You ought to worry \Nabout your own health first.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:50.98,0:28:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, don't die.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:53.59,0:28:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}cannot{\i0} die.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:55.55,0:28:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, if ever...
Dialogue: 10,0:28:58.13,0:29:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were ever to die, \NI’d rush over to your side,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:03.09,0:29:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,throw myself over you{ face down}, \Nand die with you then and there!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:06.91,0:29:09.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei depends on me that much... {unsure, maybe "prepared to go that far for me"}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:24.28,0:29:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:29.14,0:29:31.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,I absolutely will not lose!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:31.27,0:29:35.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,No matter what great hardships befall us, \Nwe will fight through them.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:35.65,0:29:39.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,As Sensei's disciple, \NI will fight with all my might!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:39.90,0:29:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:40.95,0:29:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, it's about to take off.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:43.53,0:29:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:45.15,0:29:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, we finally published it. \NRead it sometime later.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:52.94,0:29:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay strong.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:54.27,0:29:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:59.85,0:30:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey...
Dialogue: 10,0:30:02.84,0:30:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:04.49,0:30:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine. Don't worry! \NLook after the kids. {not exactly but I think that's what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:07.76,0:30:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, you need to hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:10.12,0:30:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:18.44,0:30:21.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,Reading "The Human Revolution" by Sensei {normally would italicize but this one is already in thoughts}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:21.36,0:30:26.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,let's you experience vividly \Nthe intense struggles he faced while in prison.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:26.47,0:30:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi-sensei!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:28.47,0:30:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be harsh on him! {/take care of your health}{ep1 16:28}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:33.96,0:30:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi is dead.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:41.02,0:30:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:49.16,0:30:51.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,I get it! {ep4 13:19}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:51.52,0:30:54.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Buddha is life itself!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:54.76,0:30:57.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's the quality of being alive!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:58.90,0:31:06.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sadly, I too will soon follow Makiguchi-sensei and Toda-sensei into imprisonment.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:06.85,0:31:10.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll fight with determination!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:11.95,0:31:14.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei is a lion.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:14.35,0:31:19.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,If so, as his faithful disciple, \NI also have to become a lion.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:20.17,0:31:25.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,The day of reckoning has come—\Nand it'll show if I have the lion in me.{what it takes to be a lion/to check if I truly am a lion}
